      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's true that taking a single 400mg dose every 2 hours keeps your pain management relatively consistent; however, it's still not ideal for your body's health. The risk of experiencing side effects increases with higher, more frequent doses. Your body needs time to metabolize the drug, and overlapping doses can cause a sudden spike in medication levels, potentially leading to toxicity.\n\nWhile it may feel like a quick fix to prevent pain spikes, there's a better way to manage pain and minimize risks to your health. Consider shorter intervals (4-6 hours) but stick to the typical 400-600mg dose or less. Also, exploring other pain management strategies, such as physical therapy or consulting a medical professional, may provide more effective and safer relief from your lower back pain. Remember, short-term relief shouldn't come at the cost of your long-term health.",
